  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a four-byte OpenType/TrueType tag packed as a big-endian 32-bit integer.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` wraps a 32-bit unsigned integer that encodes four ASCII characters in big-endian order, as used by OpenType and TrueType for axis tags (e.g. `'wght'`, `'ital'`) and feature tags. The first character occupies the most significant byte.

Use `SKFourByteTag.Parse` to parse a string, or construct one directly from four characters. Implicit conversions to and from `uint` allow interoperability with native code.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from four characters
var weightTag = new SKFourByteTag('w', 'g', 'h', 't');

// Parse from a string
var widthTag = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wdth");

// Use as a variation axis
var coord = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = weightTag, Value = 700f };
```
]]></format></remarks>
